.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "Holberton School" "Simple Shell"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is a basic UNIX command line interpreter.
It executes commands read from standard input.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.
Commands are executed using the PATH environment variable.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
./hsh
.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.PP
echo "ls" | ./hsh

.SH SIGNALS
Ctrl+C (SIGINT) is handled and does not terminate the shell.

.SH AUTHORS
